 Port Elizabeth - Some welcome rain was recorded over the Eastern Cape on Tuesday night. "The most welcome figures were recorded were recorded in the Adelaide Fort Beaufort are where 70 mm was recorded, Graaf Reinet which received 26 mm and Grahamstown with 40 mm," said Garth Sampson, SA Weather Service Client Liaison Officer (Eastern Cape Region). "Even the areas around Kliplaat received 23 mm and the Darlington Dam recording 41 mm. "The Port Elizabeth region recorded between 10 and 20 mm over the last 48 hours." Samson said that the catchment areas were not so lucky with only 4 mm at Joubertina, * at Kareedouw and 17 at Patensie. "The outlook is for some more scattered thunderstorms over the entire province this afternoon and some possible good falls and even flooding in the Graaf Reinet area," he described. "Flooding is expected in places over the Eastern Half of the province. "It will clear from the west later. "We must not that although this rain is most welcome it does little to alleviate our drought situation and the public MUST continue to use water sparingly." Station Names 7 8 Total Nelson Mandela Bay    AWOS Port Elizabeth Airport 1.0 11.4 12.4 ARS 3rd Ave Dip 1.8 12.6 14.4 ARS Blue Horizon Bay 4.2 5.4 9.6 ARS Chatty 0.6 20.0 20.6 AWS Coega 0.6 14.2 14.8 AWSH Fettes Road 0.6 12.6 13.2 ARS Flower Reserve 4.6 5.2 9.8 AWSH Motherwell * * 0.0 ARS Riverstone Bridge 2.2 7.6 9.8 ARS St Albans * 7.4 7.4 AWS Uitenhage 3.0 12.0 15.0 MAN Woodridge * * 0.0 Catchment   0.0 AWS Joubertina 0.2 4.2 4.4 ARS Kareedouw 2.0 5.8 7.8 Man Kareedouw 2.0 6.0 8.0 Man Kouga Dam * 13.0 13.0 AWS Patensie 3.4 13.4 16.8 Man     Other Towns    AWS Addo NIL 26.8 26.8 AWS Bisho/KWT 1.4 42.2 43.6 AWS Cape St Francis 0.4 4.2 4.6 AWS Cradock NIL 16.0 16.0 AWS East London 0.8 25.0 25.8 AWS Fort Beaufort NIL 70.2 70.2 AWS George 1.2 1.8 3.0 AWS Graaff Reinet NIL 26.0 26.0 AWS Grahamstown NIL 40.2 40.2 AWS Henry`s Flats NIL 25.8 25.8 AWS Joubertina 0.2 4.2 4.4 AWS Mossel Bay 0.2 0.6 0.8 AWS Mth